place.name: AYLMERTON
place.gazetteerText: AYLMERTON, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; near the coast, 3 miles WSW of Cromer, and 18 E of Walsingham r. station. Post Town, Cromer under Norwich. Acres, 1,679. Real property, £1,484. Pop., 250. Houses, 66. The property is divided among a few. Beacon Hill commands a fine prospect. The living is a rectory, united with the rectory of Runton, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £500. Patron, John Ketton, Esq. The church is later English, and was restored in 1865. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
